    "statementHTML": "<div class=\"statement-body\">\n<div class=\"statement-section statement-goal\">\n   <h1><span class=\"icon icon-goal\">&nbsp;</span><span>Goal </span></h1>\n   <span class=\"question-statement\">You are living in a cave on a mountain and there is no electricity. At the begining you have <var>C</var> candles. When a candle has finished to burn, it remains generally a bit of it and so, with <var>E</var> candle ends you can make one candle to survive longer. How many candles are you going to burn until you don't have enough ends of them to make other?<br><var>E</var> can be equal to <const>0</const>, in this case candles burnt don't produce usable ends.<br>If you can burn indefinitely candles, then print <const>IMPOSSIBLE</const>.</span>\n</div>\n<div class=\"statement-section statement-protocol\">\n   <div class=\"blk\">\n      <div class=\"title\">Input</div>\n      <div class=\"question-statement-input\"><strong>Line 1:</strong>The number <var>C</var> of candles at the begining<br><strong>Line 2:</strong>The number <var>E</var> of ends needed to make a new candle</div>\n   </div>\n   <div class=\"blk\">\n      <div class=\"title\">Output</div>\n      <div class=\"question-statement-output\">The total number of candles that you will be able to burn or <const>IMPOSSIBLE</const> if the cycle is infinite.</div>\n   </div>\n   <div class=\"blk\">\n      <div class=\"title\">Constraints</div>\n      <div class=\"question-statement-constraints\">0 &le; <var>C</var> &le; 9999<br>0 &le; <var>E</var> &le; 9999</div>\n   </div>\n   <div class=\"blk\">\n      <div class=\"title\">Example</div>\n      <div class=\"statement-inout\">\n         <div class=\"statement-inout-in\">\n            <div class=\"title\">Input</div>\n            <pre class=\"question-statement-example-in\">9\n3</pre>\n         </div>\n         <div class=\"statement-inout-out\">\n            <div class=\"title\">Output</div>\n            <pre class=\"question-statement-example-out\">